[SN]TITLE[SN]
Croston in danger due to River Douglas flood defence 'gap'

[SN]FIRST-SENTENCE[SN]
A breach in river defences near a Lancashire village could see it suffer further flooding, the Environment Agency has warned.

[SN]RESTBODY[SN]
Croston, which lies south of Preston, was hit by flooding at the weekend. About 50 homes remain without power.
The agency said the River Douglas south of the village had "overwhelmed" defences, causing a "gap".
Flood risk manager Andy Brown said they would be "coming up rapidly with an emergency plan" to carry out repairs.
