Electricity North West said about 500 homes in the village had lost power in the flooding, with 50 still waiting to be reconnected.
Incident manager Steve Cox said the "focus today is to ensure power is restored for the remaining customers".
South Ribble's Conservative MP Seema Kennedy said she would be asking the Government to "look again" at flood defence spending and "maybe reallocate resources in the Environment Agency and think about what we are doing, quite literally, upstream".
The Environment Agency have said flood defences across the UK need a "complete rethink" following the recent flooding.
